The paper deals with image retrieval tasks using hashing methods, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel approach using random forests and convolutional neural networks, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) aspects related to image retrieval tasks.
